The murdered man apparently lost his way on Friday night at Manzana location, Qina village in Centane, Captain Jackson Manatha said.
The man’s body was found at about 9.30am on Saturday morning. He had “an upper body injury”. A swift police investigation led to the arrest of the suspect.
The suspect would appear in the Centane Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday on a murder charge. The motive for the murder was not known, Manatha said. – African News Agency (ANA)